HEADWORD: Passible
<hw>Pas"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>passibilis</ets>, fr. <ets>pati</ets>, to suffer: cf. F.
<ets>passible</ets>. See <er>Passion</er>.]</ety> <def>Susceptible of
feeling or suffering, or of impressions from external agents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Apolinarius, which held even deity itself <qex>passible</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
